Toilet paper here is so cheap,

509
00:21:10,402 --> 00:21:12,738
I feel like I'm wiping my butt
with a cheese grater.

510
00:21:13,005 --> 00:21:13,906
Later!

511
00:21:14,406 --> 00:21:15,407
Hey!

512
00:21:16,308 --> 00:21:17,443
I‐It's a ninja...

513
00:21:18,010 --> 00:21:19,445
Why does Tom have a ninja?

514
00:21:19,845 --> 00:21:21,147
<i>You still don't get it?</i>

515
00:21:22,882 --> 00:21:24,884
<i>This</i> <i>is</i> <i>the</i> <i>truth</i> <i>behind</i>
<i>the</i> <i>Dream</i> <i>Catcher.</i>

516
00:21:25,417 --> 00:21:26,418
<i>Think back.</i>

517
00:21:26,619 --> 00:21:28,020
<i>Did he ever make a</i>
<i>dream come true</i>

518
00:21:28,020 --> 00:21:30,523
<i>that wasn't simple and easy</i>
<i>to see or provide?</i>

519
00:21:30,523 --> 00:21:31,390
<i>No!</i>

520
00:21:31,390 --> 00:21:32,758
He preinterviewed

521
00:21:32,758 --> 00:21:34,827
<i>all</i> <i>his</i> <i>followers</i> <i>and</i> <i>chose</i> <i>only</i>

522
00:21:34,827 --> 00:21:36,829
<i>dreams that were easy</i>
<i>to grant in person.</i>

523
00:21:37,229 --> 00:21:38,998
<i>He kept a ninja hidden</i>
<i>in the beams</i>

524
00:21:38,998 --> 00:21:40,933
<i>and acted as if he was</i>
<i>performing miracles</i>

525
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:42,268
<i>with a speed of light...</i>

526
00:21:42,735 --> 00:21:44,336
<i>You were all tricked by this!</i>

527
00:21:44,870 --> 00:21:45,905
Impossible.

528
00:21:45,905 --> 00:21:48,974
We would never fall for such a
simple trick as that, you know!

529
00:21:48,974 --> 00:21:50,209
Yeah, that's right.

530
00:21:50,209 --> 00:21:52,344
I was bald, but now
I have so much hair!

531
00:21:52,611 --> 00:21:53,646
Hey, this is a wig!

532
00:21:53,646 --> 00:21:54,413
It's true.

533
00:21:54,413 --> 00:21:56,682
Why the hell didn't you notice that
before, huh?

534
00:21:56,816 --> 00:21:59,885
Well, I didn't touch it 'cause I didn't
want my new hair to fall out!

535
00:22:01,253 --> 00:22:02,221
Hey, Tom, you bastard!

536
00:22:02,221 --> 00:22:03,822
How dare you trick us like that!

537
00:22:03,822 --> 00:22:05,157
Give us back our money!!

538
00:22:08,327 --> 00:22:10,196
Where do you think you're
going, Guru?

539
00:22:10,763 --> 00:22:13,165
Why don't you use your
Dream Catcher to get out of this.

540
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:16,101
‐Pray to your hairy mole for help!!
‐Pray to your hairy mole for help!

541
00:22:23,475 --> 00:22:24,843
<i>In the end, he was like us...</i>

542
00:22:25,344 --> 00:22:28,681
<i>he was just a pathetic man who</i>
<i>was blinded by his own dream.</i>

543
00:22:30,416 --> 00:22:31,217
<i>That's right.</i>

544
00:22:31,217 --> 00:22:32,518
But the only thing different,

545
00:22:32,518 --> 00:22:34,620
is whether you have people
to help you out

546
00:22:34,620 --> 00:22:36,822
and get you back up on your
feet when you sink.

547
00:22:37,223 --> 00:22:40,359
If I ever start drowning,
you'll help me out,

548
00:22:40,359 --> 00:22:41,694
won't you. Hanako?

549
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:45,297
Of course, Otae.

550
00:22:45,464 --> 00:22:48,100
Next time, I'll show you Osaka's
warm hearted spirit.

551
00:22:54,006 --> 00:22:55,474
D‐D‐Dream Catcher.

552
00:22:56,008 --> 00:22:58,177
Please let me win big at a casino.

553
00:22:58,444 --> 00:23:00,346
What are you
doing up here, Gintoki?

554
00:24:32,204 --> 00:24:34,506
<i>Hey, Gin, I want to eat</i>
<i>a steamed pork bun!</i>

555
00:24:34,873 --> 00:24:35,708
<i>I don't have any.</i>

556
00:24:35,708 --> 00:24:38,444
<i>If you want a steamed pork bun,</i>
<i>ask Santa for one.</i>

557
00:24:38,644 --> 00:24:39,511
<i>You can't fool me.</i>

558
00:24:39,511 --> 00:24:41,747
<i>Everyone knows Santa</i>
<i>doesn't really exist!</i>

